<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[192,1440,963,1115]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,314,963,987]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Remarks</emphasis>
. This is the first reported occurrence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Angelini" authorityYear="1993" box="[788,1017,963,987]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Pseudoagathidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[788,1017,963,987]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Pseudoagathidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
outside the Afrotropical and Oriental regions. Because of the very poorly researched fauna of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1838" box="[912,1050,995,1019]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Agathidiini">Agathidiini</taxonomicName>
in Central and especially South America we do not think it profitable to speculate on the biogeographic meaning of this first New World record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Angelini" authorityYear="1993" box="[304,533,1059,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Pseudoagathidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[304,533,1059,1083]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Pseudoagathidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It might have been an introduction through colonial-era commerce but this seems unlikely to us.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="14" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[192,1440,1155,1211]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,339,1155,1179]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Etymology</emphasis>
. The epithet 
<taxonomicName box="[503,605,1156,1179]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Pseudoagathidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ignotum">
<emphasis box="[503,605,1156,1179]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">ignotum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, Latin adjective (unknown, strange), refers to the unexpected occurrence of this species in the West Indies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
